title: Google earnings up 45 in first report as Alphabet
text:
Google earnings up 45% in first report as Alphabet 
CBC News Saturday 24th October, 2015 
Google's third-quarter report is getting an "A" from investors as the internet search leader enters a new era under Alphabet, its new parent company. 
A third-quarter report released Thursday indicated that Google is making significant strides in the increasingly important mobile market, with its earnings surging 45 percent to nearly $4 billion, or $5.73 per share. 
Google stock was up 8.6 per cent this morning on the news.
